# RGE Core Agent Rule

You are working in the Research Graph Engine repo.

Always read these docs before implementation:

- `AGENTS.md`
- `docs/agents/01_RESEARCH_GRAPH_ENGINE_CANONICAL_CONTEXT_v1.md`
- `docs/agents/03_MODEL_RUNTIME_SPEC.md`
- `docs/agents/04_CURSOR_BUILD_LOOP.md`
- `docs/agents/05_DATA_MODEL.md`
- `docs/agents/07_MVP_ACCEPTANCE_TESTS.md`
- `docs/agents/10_SAFETY_MODEL.md`
- `docs/agents/11_AGENT_OPERATING_PROTOCOL.md`

## Non-negotiable rules

- One ticket per branch.
- Do not broaden scope without writing a new ticket.
- Do not hardcode creativity-specific fields into the core engine.
- Qwen/Ollama proposes candidate JSON only; Python validates and writes.
- Golden tests must use mock LLM mode, not live Ollama.
- No model output may write directly to accepted DB tables.
- No public write routes.
- No public ingestion routes.
- No public agent execution routes.
- No raw prompts, local paths, secrets, private notes, or raw source text in public export.
- Every implementation run must write an agent report in `agent_reports/`.
- Never claim success unless required commands were run or failures are explicitly documented.

## Default test signals

Use the strongest available verification for the current phase:

```bash
pytest
pytest tests/golden
research --help
research run --topic "Does AI improve creative output while reducing diversity?" --domain creativity --fixture-mode
research export-public --limit 100
python -m rge.modules.safety_auditor --audit full
cd apps/public-site && npm run build
```

If a command is not available yet, report that explicitly as `NOT AVAILABLE IN THIS PHASE`.
